### I have bought this house in 1970 for two lakh.{.text-center}

* The sentence is in present perfect( have+$v_3$ ).But word the ==in + year== denotes that the sentence is in past simple form.
* Past simple form is Sub+$v_2$+obj,there is no helping verb
* Ans : I `bought` this house in 1970 for two lakh.

---

### I have had lunch one hour ago {.text-center}

* The sentence is in present perfect( have+$v_3$ ).But word the ==ago== denotes that the sentence is in past simple form.
* Past simple form is Sub+$v_2$+obj,there is no helping verb
* Ans : I `had` lunch one hour ago.
* here `had` is not $v_3$ form instead it means eating in past sense.

---

### Three years ago an earthquake had destroyed their country. {.text-center}

* The sentence is in past perfect( had+$v_3$ ).But word the ==ago== denotes that the sentence is in past simple form.
* Past simple form is Sub+$v_2$+obj,there is no helping verb
